= Signal Handling (`kernel/signal`)
:toc: left
:icons: font
:sectlinks:

See also: link:index.html[Kernel Index], link:syscall.html[Syscall], link:cpu.html[CPU]

This directory provides signal-related syscall handlers and internal signal state management.

== Summary

* Handles signal registration and dispatch semantics.
* Integrates per-process signal masks and action tables.
* Provides kernel-side implementations for signal syscalls.

== Typical Work in This Area

* Extend POSIX-like signal behavior.
* Add pending queue and delivery edge-case handling.
* Improve interaction with process lifecycle and scheduler.

